						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone built into the north prākāra of the Vīranārāyaṇasvāmin temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>(Date lost.)</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year</hi> (lost). The name of the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">• • • • • bhānu</hi> is partially preserved. Other details available are <hi rend="bold">Māgha ba. Thursday.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> is lost. The years Chitrabhānu and Svabhānu coincided with A.D. 1102-3 and 1103-4 respectively. Palaeography would also support this date, though there is nothing in the record to assign it definitely to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Vikramāditya VI.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a grant made by <hi rend="bold">Saṁkimayya-Nā[yaka]</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Mahādēvabhaṭṭa.</hi> The record is broken on the right side. Lines 18 to 23 apparently contain a separate grant.</p>						

						</summary>
